title: Billis, Rocky Mountain volleyball continue hot streaks
text:
Billis, Rocky Mountain volleyball continue hot streaks Gazette Staff 0 
HELENA -- Ahlea Billis recorded her sixth consecutive double-double and sixth-ranked Rocky Mountain College defeated Carroll College 25-22, 25-17, 23-25, 25-21 in Frontier Conference volleyball Saturday. 
It's the 11th straight win for the Battlin' Bears, who improved to 7-0 in the league and 21-4 overall. Carroll College fell to 6-1 and 15-9. 
Billis had team highs in kills (18) and digs (25). Mariah Stiffarm added 15 kills and four blocks and Sydney Matheny had 11 kills. Tori Bertsch had 50 assists. 
Paige Montgomery led the way for Carroll College with 17 kills. Tags
